An Act establishing a sick leave bank for Emily Coollick.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Notwithstanding any general or special law to the contrary, MassAbility
2 shall establish a sick leave bank for Emily Coollick, an employee of the Department. Any
3 employee of the Department may voluntarily contribute 1 or more sick, personal or vacation
4 days to the sick leave bank for use by Emily Coollick. If Emily Coollick terminates employment
5 with the Department or requests to dissolve the sick leave bank, any remaining time in the sick
6 leave bank shall be transferred to the extended illness leave bank. Sick leave bank days shall not
7 be used for absences unrelated to the illness or disability that necessitated the establishment of
8 the sick leave bank as determined by the Department.
9 SECTION 2. This act shall take effect upon its passage.
